message: [[WP:Automatic edit summaries|←]]Created page with ''''Sundown: The Future of Children and Drugs''' is an acclaimed documentary written, produced and directed by eighteen year old high school stu...'
This is getting ridiculous.  People are changing core information.    Despite the reviews, the film performed extremely well, grossing three times its $40m budget and was #1 Blue Ray and #2 DVD.
Added one line to the cast/character bio.
Added that AVP: R was nominated for MTV award for Best Fight Sequence
No one is trying to save it was critically praised.  You cover the facts clearly with MetaCritic AND Rotten Tomatoes but you can't arbitraily omit postive reviews for your own agenda.
You cannot omit parts of a positive review.  You can't do that ethically.  Entertainment Weekly gave it a B on an A to F scale.  This is fair wording. You are clearly biased.
Clarified language related to reviews WITHOUT altering any of the core information contained in the piece.  It would be good if eager-beavers would follow this example.
The ONLY information posted here is negative and not consistent with other movies on wiki.  For instance, Entertainment Weekly actually gave it a grade B.  Only thing better would have been an A.
Added DVD sales, rental numbers.  There is NO REASON to delete this.  It's as worthy as the box office numbers.
Now the good and bad reviews alternate.  You can't front load all the negative reviews.  The New York Times and Entertainment Weekly were very postive reviews and deserve equal treatment.
There were positive reviews for this film and you CANNOT continually delete the positive reviews and ONLY post the negative reviews.  It will be changed every time you do this and reported.
Why did you change all the work that was correct and which we had agreed on?  I simply want this to be correct. The link you site is broken.  I'm not in some kind of silly Wiki war with you.
I corrected a typo and clarified one sentence.   I agree with all of your other points.  Thank you for your work on this page.
I sent you a long explanation and directed you to where you can verifiy it.  Please leave this alone until you check out what I am saying.
If you "don't understand" WHY do you keep reverting to something that you are clearly unaware is wrong.  How many other pages have you done this on?  I'm going to find out because this is non-sense

You are actually contradicting the official credits on IMDB and Wiki (see the credits box on this same page) You DO NOT have the right to deny people credit they earned or to rewrite history.  STOP!!!
Not vandalism.  The issue is simple.  You are rewriting the credits for the film.  You are denying people who have credit on the film.  IMDB has the correct official credits.  Please check,

THIS IS NOT MY OPINION!  PLEASE just go to IMDB and you will confirm these facts.  These are the actual WGA credits for this film.  I don't know how to link to it but just go for yourself and see!!!!!
It was NOT an original screenplay.  Shusett and O'Bannon share story credit.  Check IMDB and Wiki.  You cannot omit their contribution.  Stop doing that!!
Anderson is the sole credited screenwriter of the screenplay for AVP.  Salerno rewrote the script during production.  Check IMDB for verification.
